name: HiTea
directions: Straight down the hallway as soon as you walk in the front door.
comment: It is a unisex/single stall bathroom with a lock and a deadbolt. Provides a urinal and a toilet. The bubble tea is good but there's a $5 card minimum so bring cash!

name: Cafe deux soleils
directions: Bottom floor in the back of the restaurant
comment: Nobody seems to care if you just walk in and use it without buying or sitting down.

name: Loyola Marymount University, Whelan residence hall
directions: 1 bathroom on each floor
comment: You have to live in the building to access it (or have a friend who lives there and can let you in).

name: Bruegger's Bagels
directions: Bathrooms located near the back one floor down. Narrow staircase near the front.  Gendered, but single occupancy.
comment: Always friendly, never had a problem with not buying anything.

name: The Screening Rooms (Cinema)
street: The Brewery, St Margaret's Road, GL50 4EF
directions: Scattered around inside (multiple bathrooms - all single stall. Not all accessible)
comment: If you don't turn right after entering (into the bar / box office part) you probably won't be noticed.

name: Whole Foods Market

name: Ilayda

comment: Anyone can use this restroom.

name: Cafe Nero

name: Ba Bar Restaurant
comment: There are 2 unisex, single stall restrooms.

name: target

name: The Handlebar

comment: You needn't necessarily be a customer to use the one by the stairs -- it's outside the restaurant itself.

name: Arby's

comment: I'm an employee here. It is safe and you won't be judged.

name: Kizuki Ramen & Izakaya

name: Missouri Hall

comment: People come to visit campus a lot during the day so it's ok if you look a little lost

name: Optimism Brewing co

name: Banshee Arts
directions: Inside Banshee Arts tattoo studio in the Firehouse Art Collective warehouse.
comment: I'm the business owner for Banshee Arts. I am supportive and happy to let anyone in need come in to access the restroom. I'm self-employed and keep somewhat irregular hours so you may sometimes find the warehouse locked if I'm not there.

name: Northwoods Animal Shelter
directions: There is one bathroom located in the hallway by the front desk, and there is one in the cat room.
comment: Just ask to use the bathroom or to go look at the animals.

name: Watson Hall, Lafayette College
directions: First floor, main lobby.

name: Starbucks
comment: Two single occupancy unisex

name: Watson Hall
directions: First floor, main lobby

name: Berkeley Public Library Tarea Hall Pittman South Branch

comment: It requires a key which is kept on a large, bright pink keychain at the staff desk...you can help yourself to the key anytime.

name: Comfort Inn lower East Side

name: Mcdonalds of Manoa Marketplace

comment: Single stall

name: Loving Hut

name: pet food express
directions: Back room
comment: Just ask where the bathroom is

name: Lawrence Hall -- School of Architecture and Allied Arts, North end of University of Oregon
directions: One on the first floor, on the North side by the art studios, to the West of the elevators labelled gender neutral. One on the third floor on the South wing, labelled "People."
comment: The building is in use at all hours, but only AAA students should be in the building after hours. During the day, anyone visiting the campus should be welcome.

name: Kern County Animal Services
directions: Outdoor near intake office. Just follow the intake sign.
comment: Since its outdoor anyone can easily go. 10am- 4pm most days

name: Triple Cities Makerspace, Inc.
directions: Restroom is by the kitchen.
comment: Triple Cities Makerspace, Inc. is a collaborative work space. The space is usually only accessible to members except for their Tuesday night open houses, when they are open to the public from 6:30pm-9:00pm. They are very accepting people and have several LGBT+ members. They have one restroom for all-genders that guests can use when they are open. The restroom is not handicap accessible.

name: Gulu Gulu Cafe
directions: in the back, to the left, through the door
comment: paying customers, I assume.

name: Whole Foods South Weymouth
directions: On the "checked out" side if the cashiers, by the kids' play area.
comment: Browse a bit either before or after you use the restroom. The employees there are awesome, and if you need a meal or a snack, they've got some great options available.

name: Trader Joe's Wine Shop
directions: In the back of the wine shop. It's a small store and it's easy to find.
comment: The TJs wine shop is separate from the grocery store. The grocery store has gendered bathrooms but the wine shop is a single stalled gender neutral bathroom. You do not have to pretend to be a customer.

name: Brick & Mortar
directions: There is no sign. For the brick and mortar from street view. You have to go up a set of stairs, and the restroom is in the back left.

name: First Church in Belmont, Unitarian Universalist
directions: Main level in classroom wing

name: Kroger's Marketplace
comment: OPEN 24/7

name: Church of Jesus Christie of Latter-day Saints
directions: Two handicapped-access single gender-neutral bathrooms, one on main level and another on lower level

name: Kroger's Marketplace
directions: On right side of building, just pasted the entrance.
comment: OPEN 24/7. so is the gas station.

name: Second Unitarian Church
comment: Unitarian universalist Churches are always safe places for trans people! If the church is open, you're certainly welcome to use the restroom regardless of your affiliation with the church

name: Target
directions: At front of store

name: New Orleans Public Library Alvar Branch
Starbucks
directions: On the far side of the café from the door, near the pickup counter
comment: Single stall, may be occupied upon one's time of arrival

name: Miss Nola's
directions: Towards the back. It's a small restraint, easy to find.
comment: I'm sure you need to be a paying customer.

name: Chomper Cafe
comment: It's a restaurant and you have to wait to be seated so you will need to order something to use the bathroom

name: Subway
directions: Walk to the back of the restaurant to find the bathroom
comment: It is a single stall and may be occupied, also you have to buy something, so just get a bag of chips, a cookie, a drink, etc., something other than a sandwich so you can just buy it quickly and use the restroom without getting in trouble

name: Target
directions: To the right of the doors as one comes in, next to customer service. The gender-neutral bathroom is the first door on the right in the hall, before the gendered restrooms; you can't miss it.
comment: It is a single-stall restroom and you may have to wait longer if it is occupied, so if it's an emergency and someone is in there you may have to use the gendered ones instead.

name: Joann Fabric and Craft
directions: All the way back and to the left.

name: House of Musical Traditions
directions: Past the front counter on the right.
comment: HMT is an independent musical instrument shop specializing in folk & world instruments. You don't have to purchase anything to use the restroom but it's worth looking around! Main level is accessible, though single stall bathroom is too small for a wheelchair to enter.

name: Mercy Main Hospital
directions: The single person bathrooms are located on floors 4 through 9 in the main tower, directly across from the visitor elevators. Additionally, on the 9th floor if you the a right out of the elevator enclosure, go forward as far as possible, take another right there is another single person stall beside the waiting room on the right. Additionally, there is a single person stall on A floor near McDonalds.
comment: All the bathrooms on the main floor have stalls, the single person bathrooms are located on the floors. None of the bathrooms in the east tower (With OB, Nursery, NICU and Surgery ICU/Waiting Rooms - near Starbucks) have single person stalls for people who are not patients or family.

name: Lakeside School
directions: Main building on campus, first floor
comment: You have to be a student or visitor on campus

name: Lantern Coffee
directions: Downstairs on the right
comment: Kind staff, good coffee and tea, gluten-free treats, LGBTQIA friendly, two levels, staff doesn't bother you if you just want a glass of water and rest.

name: District Pub
directions: Go past the restaurant part in the front and into the bar section by taking the hallway on the left of the food-ordering part. Bathrooms are all the way back on the left.

name: Republic of Pie
directions:
Go past the bar into the main room with a bunch of tables and couches. Women's room is straight ahead on the left (across from the table around a big tree). Men's room is on the other side, so go left across the room to the wall, and then down the short hallway to the right. 

The woman's room door is out in the open, but the men's room door is hidden down the hallway, so no one would see you in go/out or notice you waiting.
comment: People are always wondering around looking for people they are meeting/ looking for tables, so no one will notice you aren't a customer

name: The Sparrows
directions: Two steps at entry, in the back of the cafe
comment: Kind staff, good coffee and tea selection, good magazines. Baby changing table in restroom.

name: Grand Rapids Children's Museum
directions: Main floor
comment: Paying customers only, family restoom, barrier free, drinking fountain.

name: Pitfire Artisan Pizza
directions: Straight in the back. Looks a little like you're about to walk into a kitchen/ storage room but then there's gendered but single stall bathrooms on the right.
comment: I assume they want you to be a paying customer, but no one seems to actually care

name: AMC Atlantic Times Square
directions: Three "family" restrooms. Two next to house 6 and one next to house 4.

name: Marquette Hall--Marquette University
directions: Basement level, two separate single stall bathrooms. Right one also has a shower.
comment: Building may be closed after 9 PM if you are not MU student/faculty/staff

name: Kingfish
directions: Straight back when you walk in from the front door.
comment: You should probably buy a go drink. Cocktails are amazing.

name: NUNM Main Bld 2nd floor center hall
directions: Center hallway of 2nd floor: one single-stall restroom and one multi-stall gender-neutral shared reateoom
comment: For students, faculty, visitors
